1. Build Before Mastery
  - I dont need to fully understand something before starting
2. Every Project Needs a Minimum Version
  - Every project must have a small, buildable first version.
3. Research Has a Time Limit
  - Dont research minor projects for more than 3 hours. Dont research major projects for more than 2-3 days. 
4. Testing rule
  - No matter what type of project, after 2 hours must test or start working on the project.
5. Failure must be documented
  - Failure is the path to success. 
6. Project limit
  - Only 2 projects at a time, no more. 
7. Finished Is Better Than Perfect
  - A slightly ugly working prototype is more valuable than a perfect unfinished design.
8. Every Project Must Teach Something



Before moving an idea into “Todo,” ask:

Is there a minimum version?
Can I explain the goal simply?
Do I know the first physical step?
Can I realistically start within 2 weeks?
Am I excited to debug this when it fails?

If most answers are “no,” the project stays in Ideas.
